/PG218/XX/PR

Halleluyah!/PR

Hail, my soul, /SCT/XXHE /XXO/XXMNIPRESENT/XX!/PR

/PR

I hail /SCT/XXHE /XXI/XXNNERMOST/XX my whole life through,/PR

I sing out to my God as long as I endure./PR

/PR

Trust not in human benefactors,/PR

in mortal beings, who have no power to help./PR

/PR

Their spirit leaves, they go back to the ground,/PR

on that day, all their thoughts are lost./PR

/PR

Happy is the one who has the God of Jacob for a help,/PR

whose hopeful thought is for /SCT/XXHE /XXL/XXIVING /XXO/XXNE/XX, our God,/PR

/PR

the maker of the heavens and the earth,/PR

the seas and all that they contain,/PR

/PR

the worldòs true guardian,/PI/PR

/SCD/XXERASH/XX. םבנב וב  / Trust not in human benefactors. At first the
message catches us off guard. Do not put your trust in other people. Even
leaders--born or chosen. Then we recall that ours is a program of sacred
principles, not sacred personalities. We should not rely on the good will
of even the noblest and most generous. (The root ב  נ is the same for
noble and generous.) The principle of protecting the weak and defenseless
is far too important to entrust to any regime, ruler or promising politician.
It is a principle encoded in the very structure of the universe. It demands
our individual obedience.    /SC/XXS.P.W./XX/PR

/PR

/SCD/XXERASH/XX. The God of religion is the God we can know and experience
every time we choose to act in the spirit of moral responsibility by being
loyal, honest, just, sympathetic and creative.    /SC/XXM.M.K. (ADAPTED)/XX/PR

